Class Description: A biochemical reaction is a biochemical process that involves the conversion of at least one chemical participant (target) into another (product) by an enzyme (agent).
Related Class Description: A catalyzed reaction is a chemical reaction that is facilitated by a catalyst.

Related Class Description: A chemical reaction is a process that leads to the transformation of one set of chemical substances to another.

Related Class Description: A chemical interaction is a biochemical process in which chemical entities interact through some set of attractive forces.

Related Class Description: A process is an entity that is identifiable only through the unfolding of time, has temporal parts, and unless otherwise specified/predicted, cannot be identified from any instant of time in which it exists.

Class Description:
A series of actions or operations conducing to an end
In PMD, a process is conducted via processing nodes and has a discernable duration as part of a workflow. A process consumes objects and parameters. A process potentially generates new objects and measurements. A process is either a transformative process or a non-transformative process with respect to objects processed via a processing node. There are primarily two types of distinguishable processes: manufacture process, analysis process. A process is a series of operations that are subordinate processes.

A process is an entity that is identifiable only through the unfolding of time, has temporal parts, and unless otherwise specified/predicted, cannot be identified from any instant of time in which it exists.
